Massmart, Standard Bank, Vodacom May Move: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-07-04T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/massmart-standard-bank-vodacom-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in South  Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose for a sixth day to
its highest close in a month, adding 60.93, or 0.2 percent, to
31,925.47 in Johannesburg.  Massmart Holdings Ltd. (MSM)  : The retailer that sold a
51 percent stake to Wal-Mart Stores Inc. last month, is
scheduled to publish an update on its annual earnings. The stock
rose 37 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 53.51 rand.  SABMiller Plc (SAB)  : Foster’s Group Ltd. Chief Executive
Officer John Pollaers said the company is focusing on its
business rather than talking to SABMiller after rejecting a
A$9.5 billion ($10.2 billion) takeover bid from the world’s
second-largest brewer. SABMiller shares increased 77 cents, or
0.3 percent, to 245.77 rand.  Standard Bank  Group Ltd. (SBK SJ): Africa’s biggest lender
is seeking to buy banks in  Nigeria  and Angola to expand its
operations on the continent, the Johannesburg-based Sunday Times
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Jacko Maree.  Steinhoff International Holdings Ltd. (SHF)  : The
furniture-maker said its European unit successfully completed a
1.26 billion-euro ($1.8 billion) syndicated loan facility on
June 29. The stock declined 5 cents, or 0.2 percent, to 22.94
rand.  Vodacom Group Ltd. (VOD)  : The largest provider of
mobile-phone services to  South Africans  said an investigation of
a transmission network failure last week will help direct the
company’s investment of more than 6 billion rand ($891 million)
this year. The shares fell 35 cents, or 0.4 percent, to 83.60
rand.  The following stocks will begin trading without the right
to the latest dividends:  Crookes Brothers Ltd. (CKS SJ), DataTec Ltd. (DTC SJ), The
Foschini Group Ltd. (TFG SJ), Illovo Sugar Ltd. (ILV SJ),
Invicta Holdings Ltd. (IVT SJ), Marshall Monteagle Plc (MMP SJ),
Nampak Ltd. (NPK SJ), Taste Holdings Ltd. (TAS SJ), Telkom  South
Africa  Ltd. (TKG SJ).  Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) rose 0.6 percent to $24.99.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 2.2 percent to $41.18.
BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) increased 1.2 percent to $79.35.
DRDGold Ltd. (DROOY US) declined 1 percent to $4.79. Gold Fields
Ltd. (GFI US) fell 2.3 percent to $14.25. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) fell 0.41 percent to $12.81. Impala Platinum
Holdings (IMPUY US) gained 2 percent to $27.35. Sappi Ltd. (SPP
US) rose 1.8 percent to $5.19. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US) increased 1.2
percent to $53.51.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nasreen Seria in Johannesburg at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net  